               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-895" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-895" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-895" type="surname" value="KEMP"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-895" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE KEMP</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N 82.</hi>) I was in the Hackney-road on the 11th of August—I saw the prisoner and another one in Hackney-road—I watched them for two hours—I saw them go up to the prosecutor—the other took hold of his arm, and the prisoner took this handkerchief out of his pocket—I saw him take it partly out in the Curtain-road—I fol<lb></lb>lowed them to Worship-street, and there he took it quite out—the prose<lb></lb>cutor was drunk—I <hi rend="italic">shoved</hi> against him, and gave him a black eye.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where were you when you saw</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184108230110"></xptr>
               <p>the handkerchief taken? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About twenty yards behind—I had been following him two hours—I knocked the prosecutor down because he had been <hi rend="italic">hoaxed,</hi> and was drunk—I ran against him in catching hold of the prisoner—I saw the prisoner come from the back of Shoreditch church—I was in plain clothes—I saw him <hi rend="italic">chuck</hi> the handkerchief down—a young man took it up, and gave it to me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
